                    <span>If you have just lunch eBay and sell some items, this book will add nothing for you!! because 80% of the book contents you already know it!! it just show you step by step how to do a specific thing like registration, leaving feedback,..etc</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">An excellent "how to"  get started book.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>13</span>
                      /
                      <span>14</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-07-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As you read this you should be hearing Copelands "Fanfare for the Common   Man" since this publication was written for the common man. No jargon or computer buzz words, only plain English.  But more importantly the organization and layout was well planned and thoughtfully arranged to make it easy to follow and help is provided. For example, if a procedure is written to do certain steps on the eBay forms, a section of the exact eBay form is provided with lines leading from the text to the exact spot on the form. There are many small paragraphs for the specific function detailed with its own bold title so that it stands out on the page along with profuse illustrations and examples. <br>I suggest that the best first step is go to eBay as browser and examine how things are searched and displayed to get a feel of what eBay is all about. Then as you explore the intricacies of the steps leading up to a complete understanding of the selling requirements you will see the value of the linearly progression of the steps outlined.  <br>    It is very important to read the "READ ME FIRST" on Page ix. Do not skip the eBay basics They are the stepping stones to the deeper water of selling your items. Remember you are getting into the real world and it is populated with real people and if you make a misstep you cannot shut down and restart as you would a computer game.<br>     This book is a very valuable desktop reference but you should seriously read it before diving into the "selling" pool.</span>
                  
              
